    The evaluation above 10 keV is based on a detailed            6725 1451
 theoretical analysis utilizing the available experimental data.  6725 1451
 Coupled-channel optical model calculations with the ECIS code    6725 1451
 [Ra70] were used to provide the total, elastic, and inelastic    6725 1451
 cross sections to the first 3 members of the ground state        6725 1451
 rotational band, as well as neutron elastic and inelastic        6725 1451
 angular distributions to the rotational levels.  The ECIS code   6725 1451
 was also used to calculate neutron transmission coefficients.    6725 1451
    Hauser-Feshbach statistical theory calculations were carried  6725 1451
 out with the GNASH [Ar88],[Yo77] and COMNUC [Du70] code systems, 6725 1451
 including preequilibrium contributions.  Systematics were used   6725 1451
 to obtain parameters for the exciton preequilibrium model, with  6725 1451
 small adjustments made to improve agreement with available       6725 1451
 experimental data.                                               6725 1451
    The Gilbert-Cameron level density model was used              6725 1451
 to supplement available experimental information on low-lying    6725 1451
 levels [Gi65].                                                   6725 1451
    The Brink-Axel model [Br55],[Ax62] was used to calculate      6725 1451
 gamma-ray transmission coefficients, using gamma-ray strength    6725 1451
 function results compiled by Mughabghab [Mu84].                  6725 1451
    A description of the calculations is given in [Yo86].         6725 1451
